**No, you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** on .NET 10. That property is the .NET 9 (and earlier) bridge. On .NET 10, you configure native MTP mode in `global.json` instead:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

With this, `dotnet test` passes arguments directly to MTP (no `--` separator needed), and you can remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from your `.csproj`.

